messages.message: Not sure how this has existed for four months or if I am just doing something I shouldn’t, but `record_output` is sometimes referenced before assignment in mapper_fns: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blame/master/shared-utils/py-utils/flow/server/src/py/instabase/flow/v2/mappers/mapper_fns.py#L345
For reference, I am running an Apply Fetcher step
We can do a check for None check for record_output. The assumption is that it should be present. If none, there is an error. We can fix this if the assumption is not true anymore
Yes it will be great to catch and handle this error — even if technically it shouldn’t happen, let’s have a PR that can catch this one instead of “unexpected exception” or missing variable. Thanks!
@Aaron Vontell - Can you file a JIRA on me ? I'll fix this in the next release
